        "content": "<p>HueCodes opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13383\">PR #13383</a> from <code>HueCodes:feat/eh-frame-emission</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Add <code>ObjectBuilder::unwind_info(bool)</code>. When enabled, the emitted object gains a <code>.eh_frame</code> section with one shared CIE and one FDE per defined function, relocated against the function symbols.</p>\n<p>The implementation routes cranelift-codegen's existing <code>UnwindInfo::SystemV</code> through gimli's <code>RelocateWriter</code> into an <code>object</code>-crate section. Off by default. Supported on ELF and COFF; Mach-O and Windows unwind formats are deferred and currently no-op or error rather than emit wrong data.</p>\n<p>Closes #1282.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 595222554,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778821346
    },
